<TEXT>
<P>
A small earthquake struck 24 miles southwest of Palm Springs. There were no 
reports of damage or injury in the magnitude 3.1 temblor, which was in a remote 
desert area, said Bob Finn, a spokesman for Caltech in Pasadena. The quake was 
not related to a series of small temblors that struck last week along the San 
Jacinto fault from San Bernardino to east of Palm Springs, Finn said. 
</P>
