<TEXT>
<P>
Clarence Martis of El Sobrante has informed his employer not to expect him back 
to work Tuesday -- or ever, for that matter. Martis, 32, said he plans to 
retire after winning Saturday's $1-million jackpot in the California Lottery's 
"Big Spin." "I'm not working anymore," said the new millionaire, formerly an 
accounts officer for Qantas Airways. 
