<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PACOIMA WOMAN SAVED FROM EMPTY CESSPOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Pacoima woman was rescued by Los Angeles firefighters Sunday after she fell 
20 feet into an empty cesspool, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Rudy Esquivel, 26, fell into the cesspool in the 8500 block of North Cayuga 
Avenue about 12:45 p.m., said Pat Marek, spokesman for the Los Angeles Fire 
Department. The underground catch basin near Esquivel's home had been opened by 
Los Angeles city workers for repairs, Marek said. 
</P>
<P>
It was unclear how the accident occurred, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Esquivel suffered minor injuries and was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in 
Mission Hills, where she was treated and released, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
