<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN and DAVID CROOK, Arts and entertainment reports from the 
times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Martin Sheen won a ruling Thursday from the Nevada Supreme Court 
overturning a requirement that he post a $5,000 bond aimed at stopping a 
protest trespass at the Nevada Test Site. Sheen, active in the movement against 
nuclear testing, was forced to post the "peace bond" after saying on national 
television he would "hopefully commit civil disobedience" at the test site. In 
reversing District Judge Bill Beko of Tonopah, the Supreme Court said in its 
2-page order that prosecutors conceded that civil disobedience isn't a crime in 
Nevada. STEVE WEINSTEIN and DAVID CROOK 
</P>
