<HEADLINE>
<P>
USIU TRIES TO STAY HOT, PLAYS VERMONT TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK HAZLETINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. International University will try for its second consecutive victory 
tonight, playing host to Vermont in a men's nonconference basketball game at 
7:30 in Golden Hall. 
</P>
<P>
USIU beat St. Francis (N.Y.), 95-77, Friday for its second victory in 3 games. 
</P>
<P>
Vermont lost, 83-76, to San Diego State Saturday. Vermont (1-5) has lost its 
last 5 games. 
</P>
<P>
Only one senior will start for either team tonight. The Gulls (5-9) have no 
senior starters, while Vermont starts two freshmen and sophomore and junior 
forwards. 
</P>
<P>
Vermont's one senior starter, 6-foot 11-inch center Joe Calavita, is averaging 
16.3 points and 9.6 rebounds and has scored in double figures in 23 consecutive 
games, including 20 Saturday against San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
USIU has started 6-11, 235-pound sophomore Mike Sterner at center. Sterner, 
however, has had his problems this season and is averaging just 4 points and 4 
rebounds. Demetrius Laffitte, a 6-5 forward, leads the team in rebounding with 
10 per game. RICK HAZLETINE 
</P>
